 Blessing Ibunge in Port Harcourt The Minister of Transportation, Rotimi Chibuike Amaechi, has officially declared his intention to run for the presidency of Nigeria on the platform of the All Progressives Congress (APC) in 2023. The former Rivers State governor made the declaration Saturday (today) in Port Harcourt at a special thanksgiving service for the unity of the APC in the state and success of the party’s national convention. Details later…